title: Our NANOGrav 15 yr results highlighted as among the top scientific breakthroughs of the year by many outlets. 
---

The evidence for the presence of an isotropic nanohertz gravitational wave background was highlighted as one of the biggest scientific breakthroughs of 2023 by the following outlets:

<ul>
  <li> <a href="https://physics.aps.org/articles/v16/213">American Physical Society</a> </li>
  <li> <a href="https://www.science.org/content/article/breakthrough-of-the-year-2023#:~:text=This%20year%2C%20clinical%20trials%20found,the%20Breakthrough%20of%20the%20Year"> Science</a> </li>
  <li> <a href="https://www.nationalgeographic.com/premium/article/11-astonishing-scientific-discoveries-2023">National Geographic</a> </li>
  <li> <a href="https://www.quantamagazine.org/the-biggest-discoveries-in-physics-in-2023-20231221/">Quanta Magazine.</a> Also check out <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=580V0wRl1Lo&t=2s&ab_channel=QuantaMagazine">the video associated with this article.</a> <\li>
  <li> <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2023-12-30/the-10-most-intriguing-science-breakthroughs-of-2023">Bloomberg.com</a> </li>
  <li> Not a media outlet, but still pretty cool that <a href="https://youtu.be/tJ3ZJjqu3NQ?si=g4AlzR4PMbRUaV7X">we made Dr. Becky's list (at #1 no less)</a> </li>
<\ul>
